Bank App API notes

1. "http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/bank/v1/usercreation/" (POST)

    to create a user, enter required field such as firstname,lastname,username,
    password and create a user



2. "http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/bank/v1/login/" (POST)

    login to your account using the username and password, then Token authentication
    occure, it generate a token , using that token you can login



3."http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/bank/v1/accountcreation/" (POST)

    here you can create account by entering the field, account_type and username
    accno generate automaticaly and balance default as 0.0



4. "http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/bank/v1/deposit/<int:accno>" (POST)

    deposit amount using the api link , account number should be enter on your
    API link



5. "http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/bank/v1/withdraw/<int:accno>" (POST)

    withdraw amount using the api link , account number should be enter on your
    API link




6."http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/bank/v1/balance/<int:accno>" (GET)

    know the account balance using the API, account number should be enter
    on API link



7. 'http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/bank/v1/transaction/<int:accno>' (POST)

    you can done your transactions. the from account number on API link
    enter to_account number and amount



8. 'http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/bank/v1/trans-history/<int:accno>' (GET)

    view transaction history of current account number



9.'http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/bank/v1/trans-history/credit/<int:accno>' (GET)

    view credit transaction history of current account number



10.'http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/bank/v1/trans-history/debit/<int:accno>' (GET)

    view debit transaction history of current account number



11. "http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/bank/v1/logout/"

    logout from current user